description:
&lt;p&gt;Family &amp; Integrated Support Division are seeking a confident, experienced individual to join our busy Secretarial Team within the Obstetrics and Gynaecology department. The post reports to a Senior Medical Secretary and is for 37.5 hrs per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate a flexible, motivated approach to their work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Audio typing and word processing (RSA II or equivalent) are key skills to the post and therefore essential to all applicants. A working knowledge of Microsoft Office is also required and good communication skills, especially telephone manner. Duties for the role include direct support to Medical Staff, dealing with enquiries from internal and external agencies, working on Etrack looking at reports from the information services pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All candidates will be required to pass an audio typing test, plus English Literacy and Numeracy tests on the day of interview. (External Candidates only)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is rewarding and challenging, within a service Division, which is continually changing and reassessing its administration systems in line with an ever-modernising NHS service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Emily O&#39;Neill on 01480 416440&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
